# Verification

The following commands were used to confirm that the lab was functioning correctly.

## Verify VLANs

```cisco
show vlan brief
```

### Expected Results

* VLANs 10, 20, 30, and 99 exist.
* All configured VLANs display an `active` status.

---

## Verify Trunk Status

```cisco
show interfaces trunk
```

### Expected Results

* Trunk interface shows `trunking`.
* Encapsulation displays `802.1Q`.

---

## Verify Allowed VLANs

Expected output should include:

```text
10,20,30,99
```

under:

```text
Vlans allowed on trunk
```

---

## Verify VLAN Propagation

Expected output should include:

```text
Vlans allowed and active in management domain
10,20,30,99
```

---

## Verify Spanning Tree Status

Ensure all VLANs are forwarding traffic:

```text
Vlans in spanning tree forwarding state and not pruned
10,20,30,99
```

## Lab Outcome

The trunk link successfully carried all intended VLANs between both switches.
